                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="70r"/>
                        <persName>Farhād</persName>carrying<persName>Shīrīn</persName>and her horse. Sculptures on the rocks.</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="77v"/>A servant laying a carpet before<persName key=" http://lccn.loc.gov/n84045832 ">Khusrau</persName>'s horse as he arrives at<persName>Shīrīn</persName>'s castle. (Inscription gives the date<date notAfter="1493" notBefore="1492" calendar="#Hijri-qamari">Rajab 898</date>and a quatrain).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="110v"/>
                        <persName>Lailā</persName>and<persName>Majnūn</persName>at school. (Inscriptions: on the architrave: Hasten to prayer before food and hasten to repentence before death. Below: A believer in the mosque is like a fish in water).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
                        <locus n="114v"/>
                        <persName>Majnūn</persName>at the<name type="place">Ka'bah</name>with his father and other pilgrims. (Inscriptions: above door: Hasten to prayer before food. Above: Ḳuranic text).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="miniature">
